[2] Illinois (Macoupin County)
Date: Wed 29 Oct 2014
Source: KPLR, KTVI [summ., edited]
http://kplr11.com/2014/10/29/cdc-monitoring-whooping-cough-outbreak-in-staunton-illinois/


The CDC is monitoring a disease outbreak in Staunton, [Macoupin County] Illinois. Cases of whooping cough appear to be spreading quickly. At last report, there were 24 confirmed cases of the illness in public and private schools in Staunton. The disease got its name from the sound babies make when they have pertussis or whooping cough. Classrooms are getting a deep cleaning.

Health officials said some people in the community are on edge after a toddler recently died [in Staunton]. They want everyone to know the child's death had nothing to do with whooping cough. If a student tests positive the youngster is given antimicrobial treatment and is out of class for 5 days.

[Byline: Roche Madden]

